  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div xml:id="NA400-kiḷavi">
            <p type="edition">itu parattai taṉṉaip pukaḻntatu “muṉpu niṉṟiyātō pukaḻntavāṟu (G1: pukaḻātavāṟu) eṉiṉ niṉṟum amaiyām” eṉṟu coṉṉamaiyāṉ eṉpatu.</p>
            <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what speaks in praise of the other woman by having said: “if you say ‘what is the way of praising strength constantly?’, although standing [there] we will not be content.”</p>
            </div>
      <div xml:id="NA400">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            vāḻai meṉṟōṭu vārpuṟu pūkku</l>
<l>            nelviḷai kaḻaṉi nērkaṭ ceṟuvi</l>
<l>            ṉarivaṉa riṭṭa cūṭṭayaṟ periya</l>
<l>            viruñcuval vāḷai piṟaḻu mūra</l>
<l>            niṉṉiṉ ṟamaikuve ṉāyi ṉivaṇiṉ</l>
<l>            ṟiṉṉā nōkkamō ṭevaṉpiḻaip puṇṭō</l>
<l>            maṟaṅkeḻu cōḻa ruṟantai yavaiyat</l>
<l>            taṟaṅkeṭa vaṟiyā tāṅkuc ciṟanta</l>
<l>            kēṇmaiyō ṭaḷaii nīyē</l>
<l>            keṭuvaṟi yāyeṉ ṉeñcat tāṉē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>            O man from a village, where the dark-naped Vāḷai fish are leaping,</l>
<l rend="indent">            big ones(?), near the ornaments(?) put [there] by the cutters</l>
<l rend="indent2">            of the fields with fine sections<note place="foot">Cf. note on NA 210.1.</note> of paddy where the corn is ripening,</l>
<l rend="indent3">            where the soft plantain stems, having grown overlong<note place="foot">How to understand <term xml:lang="ta">vārpu uṟupu</term>? Easier probably is to propose an abstract noun <term xml:lang="ta">vārpu</term>, meaning something like "over-length". The TL does not give it, but <term xml:lang="ta">uṟu</term> is usually compounded with nouns, and if this were an auxiliary construction we would rather expect vārntu as absolutive.</note>, are swinging,</l>
<l>        if I be content without you, standing here,</l>
<l>        with unpleasing look, what mistake is [this]?</l>
<l>        Mingling with superior intimacy, you,</l>
<l rend="indent">            like virtue does not know of getting lost</l>
<l rend="indent2">            in the assembly in Uṟantai of the brave Cōḻars,</l>
<l>        you do not know of getting lost from my heart.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
